<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1354,1739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1499613740" collectingDate="2002" collectingDateMax="2013" collectingDateMin="2002" country="Japan" county="Yasunaga" location="East Asia" municipality="As" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" specimenCount="1">
Among thirty-one described species of genus 
<taxonomicName box="[746,899,1534,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Acrorrhinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[746,899,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Acrorrhinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Old World tropics and sub-tropics, seventeen species are known to occur in Asiatic tropics and sub-tropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Duwal" box="[979,1196,1570,1595]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Duwal, R. K., Jung, S. &amp; Lee, S. (2014) Taxonomic revision of the tribe Hallodapini Van Duzee (Hemiptera: Miridae: Phylinae) from Korea. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 17, 601 ‾ 607." type="journal article" year="2014">
Duwal 
<emphasis box="[1063,1114,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">et al</emphasis>
., 2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[1208,1353,1570,1595]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Schuh, R. T. (1984) Revision of the Phylinae (Hemiptera, Miridae) of the Indo-Pacific. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 177, 1 ‾ 476." type="journal article" year="1984">Schuh, 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<date pageId="1" pageNumber="402" value="2002" valueMax="2013">
<collectingDate pageId="1" pageNumber="402" value="2002" valueMax="2013">
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[1366,1422,1571,1595]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Schuh, R. T. (2002 ‾ 2014) On-line Systematic Catalog of Plant Bugs (Insecta: Heteroptera: Miridae). Available from: http: // research. amnh. org / pbi / catalog / (accessed 13 February 2017)" type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
– 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[151,211,1607,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Schuh, R. T. &amp; Menard, K. L. (2013) A revised classification of the Phylinae (Insecta: Heteroptera: Miridae): Arguments for placement of genera. American Museum Novitates, 3785, 1 ‾ 72." type="journal article" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
</collectingDate>
</date>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[222,483,1606,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Yasunaga, T., Yamada, K. &amp; Artchawakom, T. (2013 b) New or little known taxa of the plant bug tribe Hallodapini (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae) from Thailand, with descriptions of three new species of the genus Acrorrhinium Noualhier. Zootaxa, 3647 (3), 429 ‾ 442." type="journal article" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">
Yasunaga 
<emphasis box="[338,387,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">et al</emphasis>
., 2013b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[495,856,1606,1631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Yasunaga, T. &amp; Duwal, R. K. (2015) Further records and descriptions of the plant bug subfamily Phylinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae) from Thailand. Zootaxa, 3981 (2), 193 ‾ 219." type="journal article" year="2015">
Yasunaga &amp; Duwal 
<emphasis box="[723,772,1606,1630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). A single temperate zone inhabitant, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Acrorrhinium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexpectatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Acrorrhinium inexpectatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C987BCF44EFFB3F7B748A7609EF951:8EBF6071F44EFFB3F6FB4A486369F919" box="[475,583,1642,1667]" country="Japan" county="Yasunaga" municipality="As" name="East Asia" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">East Asia</location>
, including 
<collectingCountry box="[706,773,1643,1666]" name="Japan" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Japan</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[783,814,1643,1667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">As</collectingMunicipality>
mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation box="[979,1246,1642,1667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" refString="Yasunaga, T., Yamada, K. &amp; Artchawakom, T. (2013 b) New or little known taxa of the plant bug tribe Hallodapini (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae) from Thailand, with descriptions of three new species of the genus Acrorrhinium Noualhier. Zootaxa, 3647 (3), 429 ‾ 442." type="journal article">
<collectingCounty box="[979,1087,1643,1667]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Yasunaga</collectingCounty>
<emphasis box="[1093,1142,1643,1667]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">et al</emphasis>
. (2013b)
</bibRefCitation>
, members of this unique genus inhabit tree trunks or branches (
<figureCitation box="[660,721,1678,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1820,1842]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitat (A) and habitus images of live Asian hallodapines. A. Japanese Sakura-cherry, Prunus yedoensis, habitat of Acrorrhinium inexpectatum. B. A. inexpectatum, male adult. C. Ditto, female adult. D. Ditto, darkened variant. E. Ditto, final-instar nymph, male. F. Ditto, female. G. Hallodapus albofasciatus, macropterous male. H. Ditto, brachypterous female. I. H. kyushuensis, macropterous male. J. Ditto, brachypterous female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/570400/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A), so they often have a cryptic, mottled color pattern similar to their habitat (
<figureCitation box="[301,363,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1820,1842]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Habitat (A) and habitus images of live Asian hallodapines. A. Japanese Sakura-cherry, Prunus yedoensis, habitat of Acrorrhinium inexpectatum. B. A. inexpectatum, male adult. C. Ditto, female adult. D. Ditto, darkened variant. E. Ditto, final-instar nymph, male. F. Ditto, female. G. Hallodapus albofasciatus, macropterous male. H. Ditto, brachypterous female. I. H. kyushuensis, macropterous male. J. Ditto, brachypterous female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/570400/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
B–F).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
